  "prompt": "Can I put a sleep number matress on a platform frame?",
  "response": "Yes, you can put a Sleep Number mattress on a platform frame, but there are a few important considerations:\n\n1. Solid support: The platform frame should have a solid, flat surface with minimal gaps between slats to provide proper support for the Sleep Number mattress.\n\n2. Slat spacing: If the platform frame has slats, they should be no more than 2-3 inches apart to prevent sagging and ensure even support.\n\n3. Boxspring alternative: Sleep Number mattresses typically don't require a boxspring, so a platform frame can work well as a direct base.\n\n4. Air chamber support: Ensure the platform frame provides consistent support for the air chambers inside the mattress.\n\n5. Manufacturer recommendations: Always check the specific guidelines for your particular Sleep Number mattress model, as recommendations can vary slightly.\n\n6. Additional support: If the platform frame seems too flexible, you might want to add a solid platform or bunkie board for extra stability.\n\nTo be absolutely certain, it's best to consult the Sleep Number customer support or check the mattress's specific installation instructions for your exact model.",
